<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="484" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1045,1287]" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1081,1107]" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">Habitat.</emphasis>
Knowledge regarding this species is based on only a few specimens (
<bibRefCitation author="Estevez, A. L. &amp; Schnack, J. A." box="[1096,1386,1081,1107]" pageId="33" pageNumber="484" pagination="59 - 61" refId="ref50081" refString="Estevez, A. L. &amp; Schnack, J. A. (1981) Descripcion de una nueva especie del genero Nerthra Say (Hemiptera, Gelastocoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 39, 59 - 61. [1980]" type="journal article" year="1981">Estévez &amp; Schnack 1981</bibRefCitation>
; Estévez 
<emphasis box="[221,280,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">et al.</emphasis>
2003, 2010). Nothing is known about its habitat associations, except that it was found in the INR, moving or resting among the flooded grass, aquatic rooted plants, or on the bottom in the Laguna Iberá (
<bibRefCitation author="Estevez, A. L. &amp; Lopez Ruf, M. L. &amp; Hernandez, E. P." pageId="33" pageNumber="484" pagination="61 - 64" refId="ref49861" refString="Estevez, A. L., Lopez Ruf, M. L. &amp; Hernandez, E. P. (2010) Description of the preimaginal instars of Nerthra gaucha Estevez- Schnack (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gelastocoridae). Zootaxa, 2444 (1), 61 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2444.1.5" type="journal article" year="2010">
Estévez 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). They were also observed submerged, walking or resting among the aquatic plants or on the bottom, and swimming on the water surface with their fore legs folded and propelled by their middle and hind legs (Estévez 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="484">et al.</emphasis>
2003, 2010).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
